 <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>God is described in the Bible as killing people for no good reason<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
&quot;For no good reason&quot;  is an assumption of the writer that he can know a reason for all that God does.  Agreeing with what Trish said above, unless you have some understanding of God's sovereignty, you're not going to understanding some if not most of what He did when He did it.  Unless someone can open their mind up to the fact that God created therefore He can pretty much destroy if He wants to because He is sovereign and has all authority to do such.  If you're not open to that possibility, then don't continue reading as your not open to any answers given to you either.  <br>
